<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Breakaways From Ruling HDZ Form New Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Breakaways From Ruling HDZ Form New Party </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mesic Elected Chairman </H4>

<F P=102> LD3004160994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The founding assembly of the Croatian Independent 
Democrats [HND] was held at Zagreb Fair today. Stjepan Mesic 
was elected chairman, while Josip Manolic, Slavko Degoricija, 
Perica Juric, Tomislav Duka, and Dragutin Hlad were elected 
deputy chairmen. A news conference was held after the founding 
assembly. Jasminka Bogdanic reports: 
  [Bogdanic] At the news conference, Stjepan Mesic, chairman 
of 
the Croatian Independent Democrats, explained the reasons for 
forming this new party on the Croatian political scene and 
presented its guidelines. 
  [Begin Mesic recording] What we want to achieve by forming 
this party is for a law-governed state to function, for Croatia 
to join Europe's processes of integration, for our system to 
become compatible as soon as possible with developed European 
democratic systems and, finally, to correct what has been wrong 
in policy, which is the attitude toward Bosnia-Herzegovina. Now 
there are attempts to block the implementation of the Washington 
agreement. We want that agreement to be honored and 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to remain a single country. [end recording] 
  [Bogdanic] Stjepan Mesic said that with respect to foreign 
policy, the HND will contact and cooperate with all European 
parties which have the word democratic in their names. 

</TEXT>

