BFN 

  [Text] The Hungarian and Slovak prime ministers have met in 
Komarom. As planned originally, no agreement has been signed at 
the talks between Peter Boross and Jozef Moravcik. However, the 
two discussed the situation of the Hungarian minority in 
Slovakia, the Boes [Gabcikovo] Dam, the elimination of double 
taxation, and the opening of new border crossing points. 
  At the joint news conference it was said that the greatest 
achievement of these Hungarian-Slovak prime ministerial talks is 
that a new phase will begin in bilateral relations. The meeting 
made possible the settlement of the disputed issues at a later 
stage, it was said at the press briefing. 

</TEXT>

