<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Continuing Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Continuing Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Brown Coal Miners To Suspend Action </H4>

<F P=102> LD3004081394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0700 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Konin, 30 Apr--The strike in the brown coal mines 
will be suspended beginning with the second shift on 30 April. 
This decision was made on Saturday morning in an agreement 
concluded between the Brown-Coal Mines Solidarity's National 
Strike Committee and the government, represented by Marek Pol, 
minister of industry and trade. 
  The strike action will be halted after joint decisions are 
reached by the Trilateral Commission on the national demands put 
forward by the strike committee and after the government 
presents a timetable for implementing these demands. 

</TEXT>

