<H4>    Solidarity Suspension of Strikes Possible </H4>

<F P=102> LD3004100394 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
0800 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Solidarity leader Marian Krzaklewski has said that, 
if the government presents in the coming days a timetable for 
meeting the union's demands, Solidarity will suspend the strike 
action scheduled for 4, 5, and 6 May. 
  In his remarks for "Signals of the Day," Krzaklewski 
stressed, however, that the action would be suspended and not 
called off. It will eventually be called off when the 
government begins to implement agreements jointly reached with 
Solidarity. 
  The Solidarity leader again accused the government of 
causing 
the strikes by not meeting earlier promises as well as of 
intentional dragging out the negotiations with the strikers. 

</TEXT>

