<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   MSZDP To Support Socialists in First Round </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZDP To Support Socialists in First Round </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205195294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] In constituencies where the Social Democratic 
Party of Hungary [MSZDP] has not put forward its own candidates, 
it is going to support the Hungarian Socialist Party. Edit 
Schranz reports: 
  [Schranz] The MSZDP wants to establish a strong left wing in 
Hungary. Without a strong left wing, serious decisions cannot 
be made in parliament. Moreover, should the occasion arise, a 
strong left wing is needed to govern the country, party Chairman 
Zoltan Kiraly said. [passage omitted] 
  The MSZDP is planning to make a decision on where and with 
whom to conclude election agreements in the second round of the 
elections at its presidium meeting to be held on 14 May. In 
connection with this, Zoltan Kiraly also revealed that, with the 
exception of left and right extremists, they might conclude 
election agreements with other parties, including liberal 
parties. For that matter, the party asks the voters to vote for 
the Socialists' list in constituencies where the MSZDP does not 
have a party list in the first round, the chairman said. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

