<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   KNSB Adopts Measures, Prepares for Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KNSB Adopts Measures, Prepares for Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904172694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2904172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 29 April, the Executive Council of the 
Confederation of Independent Trade Unions in Bulgaria [KNSB] 
adopted a package of urgent measures aimed at overcoming the 
destabilization of the financial system and the crisis in income 
and production. An appendix to the package was adopted which 
demands the government inform the parliament and the trade union 
about commitments to international institutions, which affect 
production in Bulgaria. 
  The Executive Council will convene the KNSB Coordinating 
Council on 9 May. The goal is to report the result of the 
warning strike and national protest rallies, conducted by 6 May, 
to update the assessment of the sociopolitical situation in the 
country, and determine the KNSB attitude toward the government. 

</TEXT>

