<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Stresses Implementing Washington Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman Stresses Implementing Washington Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205181194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Tudjman has replied to a letter from Alija 
Izetbegovic, president of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency. The 
following is the text of the president's reply: 
  I have received your letter confirming an interest in the 
speedy and comprehensive implementation of the Washington 
agreement. I maintain that it can already be said that since 
the agreement was signed Bosniak-Croatian relations have been 
developing in a positive way and that on the whole we can be 
satisfied with initial results. 
  I agree with you, however, that everything should be done to 
implement as soon as possible the agreement in its entirety and 
that those impeding this positive process on either side should 
be neutralized. I firmly believe that it is possible and 
necessary to resolve all the issues you mentioned to our mutual 
satisfaction. I again stress that you can fully rely on all my 
influence in order to fully implement as soon as possible the 
agreements signed in Washington. 
  I believe that my visit to Sarajevo will take place soon and 
I am ready to travel as soon as this is technically possible. I 
believe that this visit will facilitate quicker solutions of all 
open issues and the further development of mutual understanding 
and cooperation between the Croatian and the Bosniak-Muslim 
people and between the federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the 
Republic of Croatia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

