<H3> <TI>   Right-Wing Parties Form New Bloc </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Right-Wing Parties Form New Bloc </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205181094 Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 29 Apr 94 p 48 </F>
<F P=103> AU0205181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Right-Wing Parties Are Creating a New </F>
Bloc"] 
  [Text] Zagreb -- As stated by the Croatian National 
Democratic League, right-wing Croatian parties held a meeting in 
Zagreb on Thursday [28 April]. These were the Croatian 
State-Creating Movement (HDP), the Croatian Democratic Party 
(HDS), the Croatian Democratic Party of Rights (HDSP), the 
Croatian Liberation Movement (HOP), the Croatian Republican 
Community (HRZ), the Croatian Party (HS), the Croatian Party of 
Rights (HSP), the Party of Croatian State Rights (SHDP), and the 
Croatian National Democratic League (HNDL). 
  The parties agreed in principle on the creation of a bloc of 
Croatian national, rights-oriented, state-creating, and 
right-wing parties so that they could jointly appear and act in 
public in the future, proceeding from Croatia's state and 
national interests. According to the statement, they discussed 
the political situation in detail. 

</TEXT>

