<F P=103> LD0205101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The issuing of certificates, which are very closely 
linked to the customs union between the Czech and Slovak 
Republics, has political aspects, too, although the economic 
aspects prevail. 
  This is what Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik said in 
connection with the problem surrounding certificates required 
for foodstuffs imported from the Czech Republic into Slovakia. 
At the same time, he said that what is important is that the 
two sides have a political interest in preserving mutual 
cooperation and mutual links at least at the present level. He 
did not rule out the possibility, however, that the current 
cooperation in this form could cease to be convenient for either 
side. 

</TEXT>

