<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Customs Union and the Payments Agreement with 
the Czech Republic are disadvantageous for Slovakia in many 
respects. This is what Slovak Deputy Prime Minister Brigita 
Schmoegnerova said at a news conference in Bratislava today. 
She said, however, that the one to blame for this situation is 
not the Czech partner, which is naturally asserting its own 
interests, but the former Slovak Government, which was not 
properly prepared to conclude these agreements. Schmoegnerova 
added that the Slovak Cabinet will deal with this issue in the 
near future. 

