<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Minister of Industry Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian Minister of Industry Arrives for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704132094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1000 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2704132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, on the invitation of Dumitru Popescu, 
the minister of heavy industry, Mr. [Mohammad Hadi] 
Nezhad-Hoseynian, the minister of heavy industries of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran, arrived in our country. Mr. 
Nezhad-Hoseynian is also chairman of the Iranian party attending 
the 10th session of the Joint Romanian-Iranian Commission, which 
is scheduled to take place in Bucharest over the next few days. 
  After his arrival at the airport, the Iranian guest stated 
exclusively to our reporter that the volume of the exchange of 
goods between Romania and Iran is the highest compared to 
similar exchanges with all other East European countries. 
  Upon turn, Industry Minister Dumitru Popescu stated that 
they 
will also approach new ways of cooperation between the two 
countries, as well as the furthering of Romanian exports. 

</TEXT>

