<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bilateral Ties Expanded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bilateral Ties Expanded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0105214694 Tehran IRNA in English 2131 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0105214694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 1, IRNA -- Iran's Minister of Heavy 
Industries Mohammad Hadi Nejad-Hoseynian and Romanian Prime 
Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu exchanged views Saturday in their 
meeting in Bucharest. 
  Vacaroiu praised Iran as his country's greatest partner in 
the Middle East and called for further expansion of ties between 
the two countries. 
  Vacaroiu said that for expanding bilateral trade-exchange, 
vouchers of investment and waiving of taxes should be signed 
first between the two sides. 
  He also said that establishment of Tehran-Bucharest joint 
venture can help further expansion of ties to make it possible 
for expanding the work in a third country. 
  Describing the broadening relations between Iran and 
Romania, 
Nejad-Husseinian referred to existance of over 900 Iranian 
active companies in Romania and asked for further facilities to 
be granted to them by the Romanian officials to pave the way for 
their further activities. 

</TEXT>

