<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Envoy Briefs Matinchev on Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Envoy Briefs Matinchev on Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904154294 Sofia BTA in English 1531 GMT 29 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2904154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, April 29 (BTA) -- Iraqi government special 
envoy Abd-al-Amir al-Anbari today met with Deputy Prime Minister 
Evgeni Matinchev, briefing him on Iraq's compliance with UN 
Security Council recommendations for the reparation of damage 
caused by the Gulf War. Mr. Anbari is here to prepare a session 
of the Bulgarian-Iraqi Committee on Trade and Economic 
Cooperation. 
  The visitor said Iraq was strictly compliant with UN 
requirements, yet the United Nations has not yet lifted the 
embargo inflicting irreparable damage on the Iraqi economy and 
people. He said the embargo has had an adverse impact on 
countries directly or indirectly linked to that war, including 
Bulgaria. Anbari said that after lifting the sanctions, Bulgaria 
and Iraq can resume cooperation in trade, construction and 
industry. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Matinchev recalled that as a result of 
the strict observance of the four-year long embargo, Iraq has 
run up a $3,250 million debt to Bulgaria. 

</TEXT>

