<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Criticizes Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Party Criticizes Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904181994 Prague CTK in English 1742 GMT 29 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2904181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ostrava, North Bohemia, April 29 (CTK) -- The 
government coalition, with the help of some political parties, 
is starting to implement measures aimed at weakening the 
Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia (KSCM), KSCM Chairman 
Miroslav Grebenicek told journalists today. He said he believed 
that the proposed amendment to the law on political parties was 
advantageous mainly for small and formerly non-existent parties. 
"Those who will support the amendment and thus demonstrate their 
accommodating approach will be richly rewarded," Grebenicek 
said. He added that at the same time these parties would make 
it clear that they place power and money above the obligations 
of the deputies of the legislative body which ensue from the law. 
  If the bill is passed and makes it possible to freely 
dissolve political parties then it would be a definitive full 
stop on the time in which citizens could cherish illusions about 
the existence of parliamentary democracy in the Czech Republic, 
he said. On the occasion of the 49th anniversary of the 
liberation of Ostrava from Nazi occupiers KSCM representatives 
today laid wreaths and bouquets of red carnations on the graves 
of fallen Red Army soldiers in the Comenius Park and at a 
memorial tank. 

</TEXT>

