<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Gazette Publishes 1993 Party Budgets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Gazette Publishes 1993 Party Budgets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205143994 Budapest MTI in English 1300 GMT 2 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0205143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 2 May (MTI) -- Last year, the Hungarian 
Democratic Forum (MDF) and the Federation of Young Democrats 
(Fidesz) had the largest takings, HUF [Hungarian forints] 1.266 
billion and HUF939 million, respectively, according to the 45th 
issue of the official gazette MAGYAR KOZLONY, which published 
information on the 1993 balances of several parties. Most of 
the money for the MDF and the Fidesz came from selling 
self-owned real estate: The MDF drew HUF832 million this way, 
while there was HUF697 million for the Fidesz. 
  The total drawings of the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP) 
amounted to HUF429 million last year, of the Alliance of Free 
Democrats (SZDSZ) HUF300 million, and of the Christian 
Democratic People's Party (KDNP) HUF150 million. The MSZP's 
budget includes a HUF225 million item of income without any 
source mentioned. 
  A total of HUF296 million in state subsidies was granted 
last 
year to the MDF, 270 million to the SZDSZ, 170 million to the 
MSZP, and nearly HUF100 million to the KDNP. The MSZP took over 
HUF18 million in membership fees, while the MDF received HUF9 
million, the SZDSZ 5 million and the KDNP 4 million. FIDESZ 
members paid altogether HUF653,000 last year. 

</TEXT>

