<H3> <TI>   Transportation Agreement Signed With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transportation Agreement Signed With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904184994 Warsaw PAP in English 1731 GMT 29 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2904184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, April 29 -- Polish and Russian transport 
ministers signed in Warsaw on Friday [29 April] a memorandum on 
the development of cooperation in transport between Poland and 
the Russian Federation. The memorandum envisages that the two 
countries will set up a joint committee to prepare a policy on 
road, air, sea transport as well as inland waters transport. 
According to Russian Transport Minister Vitaliy Yefimov, the 
lack of money does not allow for the realisation of transport 
investments such as the construction of highways and border 
crossings. The Russian minister said that Russia would decrease 
fees for flights over its territory which are higher than the 
prices of the ICAO (International Civil Aviation Organisation). 
Yefimov denied that Russian prices are higher. 

</TEXT>

