<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily `Apologizing' to Meciar on Affair Story </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily `Apologizing' to Meciar on Affair Story </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305124494 Prague CTK in English 1025 GMT 3 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0305124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, May 3 (CTK) -- The editorial staff of 
the Bratislava evening paper VECERNIK are apologizing to 
ex-Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar and the former director of his 
secretariat, Anna Nagyova, for publishing on April 26 an article 
headlined "Will Vladko Be Rocking the Cradle?", the daily 
REPUBLIKA writes today. 
  Last week VECERNIK wrote that "the love, kept secret for 
several years, between Vladko (diminutive for Vladimir) and his 
right hand Anicka (diminutive for Anna) who until very recently 
were calling the shots in the political heavens is to bear 
well-deserved fruit for the benefit of our country in five or 
six months." 
  "It is true that we have published something in small 
italics, written in a considerably ironical manner, and 
headlined Will Vladko Be Rocking the Cradle?, on April 26, 
without mentioning specific," but making it possible to guess 
that it concerned the above mentioned figures, VECERNIK 
confessed. 
  The paper called on the Austrian Press Agency APA to publish 
a denial of its report, in which it cited the full names of 
former Slovak ex-Prime Minister and director of his secretariat, 
referring to the VECERNIK story. A spokesman of Meciar's 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) said that "Austria was 
interfering with the election campaign in Slovakia in the 
dirtiest possible way." 

</TEXT>

