<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Agreement Signed With Malaysia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Agreement Signed With Malaysia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0205135294 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in English 
1300 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0205135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Malaysia and Albania have signed a landmark 
memorandum of understanding [MOU], paving the way for Malaysian 
military officers to train the soldiers of the former communist 
republic. For a start, Malaysia has agreed to train 25 Albanian 
officers this year. The MOU was signed by Defense Minister 
Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak and his Albanian counterpart Encik 
[Mr.] Safet Zhulali in Tirana, Albania. Under the MOU, 
Malaysian and Albanian armed forces will also hold exchange 
programs and joint exercises, cooperate in the fields of science 
and technology, as well as embark on business cooperation in the 
defense industry. Datuk Sri Najib said Malaysia would also 
assist the Eastern European state in the modernization and the 
upgrading of its armed forces. Speaking at the signing 
ceremony, he said the MOU would pave the way for closer 
cooperation between the two countries. Briefing Malaysian 
journalists later, he said Malaysia had approved a special fund 
of 2.6 million ringgit to assist in the development of the 
Albanian Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

