<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reportedly Continue Attacks in Bihac </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Reportedly Continue Attacks in Bihac </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305101294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0305101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] Karadzic's terrorists continued attacks on the 
Bihac district in the last 24 hours. The defenders on the Bihac 
section of the front, the Grmusko-Srbljanski plateau, and the 
Bosanska Krupa and Buzim areas are constantly being attacked 
with anti-aircraft weapons and heavy machine guns. They shelled 
indiscriminately the front lines of defense and civilian targets 
with 82-mm and 120-mm mortars several times during the night. 
  Members of the Kladusa paramilitary army did not keep still 
either. Their artillery in Golubovici was particularly active. 
They shelled farmers working in the fields. They inflicted 
substantial damage and killed a large number of cattle in the 
villages around Todorovo and Varoska Rijeka. 
  They also carried out mortar and gun attacks and tried to 
provoke infantry attacks on other lines of separation. The 
increasing rift in Abdic's private army is illustrated by the 
fact that they have recently been carrying out mobilizations in 
Velika Kladusa, particularly for the police force. Out of 800 
people invited to join the force, only two reported. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-54636 </DOCNO>
