Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Attacks on Serbian Positions Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Attacks on Serbian Positions Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205114594 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1108 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0205114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, May 2 (TANJUG) -- Strong Moslem artillery 
attacks on Teslic, Serb-held town in northern Bosnia, on Monday 
caused huge material damage, Bosnian Serb army sources have 
said. The Moslems also launched mortar and infantry attacks on 
Serb settlements and positions close to Doboj and in the region 
of Mt. Trebava and infantry and artillery attacks in the area of 
Mt. Ozren (all in northern Bosnia) the sources said. The 
Bosnian Serb army was forced to strongly respond to the attacks, 
it was said. Four civilians, wounded in Sunday's artillery 
shelling of Doboj which killed four civilians, are out of 
danger, the Bosnian Serb army said. 
  The Doboj Serbs have over the past month been under constant 
Moslem fire which killed many civilians, but the shelling of 
this town fails to draw the attention of the world public and of 
the U.N. Protection Force. The Moslem offensive in northern 
Bosnia aims to cut the corridor which links the eastern and 
western parts of the Bosnian Serb republic (RS). On Sunday and 
Monday NATO planes have constantly been flying over Bihac 
(western Bosnia) thus encouraging the Moslems to mount mortar 
and infantry attacks on Serb positions, the Bosnian Serb army 
sources warned. 
  On Monday the Moslems opened anti-aircraft and sniper fire 
on 
Bosnian Serb army positions in the upper parts of the Neretva 
River valley, while the regular Croatian army units launched 
mortar attacks on the Bosnian Serbs near trebinje (southern 
Bosnia), it was said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

