<H3> <TI>   UN Troops `Guzzling' With Serbs in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Troops `Guzzling' With Serbs in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305104794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0305104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahrudin Becic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] The situation in Gorazde remains unchanged. The 
chances of the aggressor moving outside the 3-km zone on the 
right bank of the Drina River are slim. UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] has not set its points in that area again today. 
Instead of performing the duties for which they have been sent, 
the UN soldiers are often guzzling with the chetniks. Twelve 
thousand people are still waiting for things to move from the 
standstill and to at least move from the 3-km zone to their 
burned homes. 

</TEXT>

