<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decision Made on Repayment of IMF Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Decision Made on Repayment of IMF Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305165894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1600 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The economic ministers decided today to pay off 
part of the debt to the IMF. Editor Vladislav Kulhavy reports 
from the government office: 
  [Kulhavy] It is a sum to the value of $430 million. 
According to Dr. (Holman), adviser to the Czech Government, the 
state can afford this extraordinary repayment for 1995 in view 
of the high foreign currency reserves of the Czech National 
Bank. This extraordinary repayment of part of the debt will, at 
the same time, mean considerable savings. [passage omitted] 
  The ministers also agreed to establish two new independent 
customs zones, in Decin and Temelin. 
  Apart from that, the meeting accepted a decision to 
privatize 
Kablo Velke Mezirici in the form of a public competition and 
agreed with the principles for further talks on creating a free 
trade zone with Romania. The ministers' meeting referred the 
materials on apprentice training for further revision. 

</TEXT>

